{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Often, either because there is no data or because the data doesn\rquote t match the search criteria, the end user will end up in a situation where there are no records in the data view. In this circumstance, the user is confronted with a blank screen, and the user may be confused about what to do next.\par
\par
In this example, two options are shown to handle this situation. The first example shows a "Query" list, with buttons to handle adding the first record.\par
\par
The second example shows a multi-purpose screen, which allows modification of the record on the same screen. In this example, Event handlers are used to simplify mode modification for the user.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 This list is opened in Query mode, and does not allow modification.\par
\par
Buttons at the bottom allow the user to add, modify, or delete existing records. The Modify and Delete buttons are disabled when the data view is empty.\par
\par
No records are locked on this list, and the data source is opened in Read Only.\par
}
